Sunday Aborisade, Abuja THE Chairman, Peoples Democratic Party National Campaign Council for Ondo State Governorship Election, Seyi Makinde, has vowed that the party would prevent the All Progressives Congress from using violence to truncate the will of the people in the state. Makinde, who is also the Governor of Oyo State, according to a statement titled, ‘PDP will protect democracy, peoples will in Ondo -Makinde…Dont allow APCs violence, threats prevent you from voting…’ signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Taiwo Adisa, on Sunday, said the PDP would protect democracy and the people’s will in the state. The governor said this shortly after a meeting with the Assistant Inspector General of Police and the Commissioner of Police in charge of the state. He accused the Ondo State chapter of the APC of masterminding electoral violence to subvert the will of the voters. Makinde appealed to the people of the state not to allow the violence being unleashed by the APC to affect their resolve to vote for the candidate of the PDP, Mr. Eyitayo Jegede (SAN). He urged them to send the APC and their representatives out of the Alagbaka Government House on Saturday. Copyright PUNCH.
